description._content: Catalog #: 09_01767 Title: Frederick A. Hoover Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Unidentified pilot in cockpit of Curtiss JN-4D ""Jenny"" aircraft, Frederick A. Hoover was the 100th individual to receive his aviator license (June 8th 1912). He performed stunts in air shows and was known as 'The Death Cheating Aviator"". He was a member of the Early Birds of Aviation. Corporation Name: Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company Tags: Frederick A.
